---
name: sentinel
version: "0.1.5"
description: AI-powered contextual security auditing — red-team-grade SAST, taint flow, attack graphs, exploit chains
author: Wembie
repo: https://github.com/Wembie/Sentinel
license: MIT
mcp_server:
  command: uv
  args: ["run", "--project", "~/.sentinel", "python", "-m", "sentinel.mcp"]
  transport: stdio
install:
  bash: "curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Wembie/Sentinel/main/install.sh | bash"
  powershell: "irm https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Wembie/Sentinel/main/install.ps1 | iex"
skills:
  - skills/sentinel-audit/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-surface/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-trace/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-attack-graph/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-logic/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-review/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-diff/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-exploit-chain/SKILL.md
  - skills/sentinel-harden/SKILL.md
agent_files:
  - CLAUDE.md
  - AGENTS.md
  - GEMINI.md
  - .cursor/rules/sentinel.mdc
  - .windsurf/rules/sentinel.md
  - .clinerules/sentinel.md
  - .github/copilot-instructions.md
  - .codex/instructions.md
---
